@startuml
autonumber
box "Orchestration Layer" #LightCyan
participant "Camunda Engine" as Camunda
participant "Kong Gateway" as Kong
end box
box "Microservice Layer" #LightYellow
participant "Flexibility Forecasting MS" as ForecastMS
participant "Flexibility Event MS" as FlexMS
end box
box "AI Layer" #LightBlue
participant "Ollama Server\n(EC2 - LLM)" as Ollama
end box
box "Persistence Layer" #LightGreen
database "AWS RDS\n(Flexibility DB)" as FlexDB
database "AWS RDS\n(Forecasting DB)" as ForecastDB
end box

== Flexibility Forecasting (AI) ==

Camunda -> Kong: Trigger Flexibility Forecasting
Kong -> ForecastMS: POST /forecast/analyze

ForecastMS -> Kong: GET /flexibility-events/logs
Kong -> FlexMS: Forward GET /flexibility-events/logs
FlexMS -> FlexDB: JDBC SELECT flexibility_event logs
FlexDB --> FlexMS: 200 OK {unstructured text logs}
FlexMS --> Kong: 200 OK {unstructured text logs}
Kong --> ForecastMS: 200 OK {unstructured text logs}

ForecastMS -> Kong: REST POST /api/generate\n{logs}
Kong -> Ollama: Forward REST POST /api/generate
note right: Prompt: Analyze log text to determine\nsentiment and if the command\nresulted in a 'Grid Stable' state.
Ollama -> Ollama: Compute Sentiment \n& Success Rate
Ollama --> Kong: 200 OK {sentiment, successProbability}
Kong --> ForecastMS: 200 OK {sentiment, successProbability}

ForecastMS -> ForecastDB: JDBC INSERT ai_insights\n(id, sentiment, successProbability, timestamp)
ForecastDB --> ForecastMS: 200 OK

ForecastMS -> Kong: Sentiment Generated\n{sentiment, successProbability}
Kong -> FlexMS: Sentiment Generated\n{sentiment, successProbability}

ForecastMS --> Kong: 201 Created {forecastId}
Kong --> Camunda: Forecasting Complete
@enduml